# Library Seat Management App – Final Requirements Document

## 1. Project Overview
**Project Name**: Library Seat Management System  
**Purpose**: Manage library seat reservations, student enrollment, fee tracking, and seat assignments for a library with 160 seats.  
**Platform**: Mobile App (iOS/Android) with offline support  
**Users**: 3 library administrators with individual credentials and defined permissions  
**Initial Seat Capacity**: 160 seats (expandable)

## 2. Functional Requirements

### 2.1 User Authentication & Sync
- **AU-01**: Individual login credentials for each user (3 separate accounts)
- **AU-02**: Multi-device real-time synchronization
- **AU-03**: Role-based permissions (One Admin and Two Employees)
- **AU-04**: Auto-sync when internet connection is restored
- **AU-05**: Session management and secure logout

### 2.2 Seat Management
- **SM-01**: Display and manage 160 seats initially
- **SM-02**: Add more seats feature (unlimited expansion capability)
- **SM-03**: Show real-time count of enrolled vs. unenrolled seats
- **SM-04**: Display actual seat numbers with visual status indication
- **SM-05**: Seat status check by entering seat number
- **SM-06**: Prevent double booking of seats
- **SM-07**: Color-coded seat display:
  - Red = Reserved
  - Green = Available
  - Yellow = Temporarily unavailable (maintenance)
- **SM-08**: Bulk seat management options

### 2.3 Student Management (Restricted Permissions)
- **ST-01**: Add new student records with:
  - Full name
  - Contact information
  - Admission date
  - Assigned seat number
  - Guardian/parent details (optional)
- **ST-02**: Edit existing student information (All users can edit)
- **ST-03**: Delete/archive student records when they leave library
- **ST-04**: Retain historical student records for minimum 2 years
- **ST-05**: Search students by:
  - Name
  - Seat number
  - Contact number
  - Admission date range
- **ST-06**: Import/export student data (CSV format)

### 2.4 Seat Assignment
- **SA-01**: Assign specific seat to specific student
- **SA-02**: View student-seat mapping with filtering options
- **SA-03**: Reassign seats when students leave
- **SA-04**: Validation to prevent seat conflicts
- **SA-05**: Temporary seat holds (up to 7 days)
- **SA-06**: Seat swapping between students

### 2.5 Fee Management (Restricted Permissions)
- **FM-01**: Track admission fee per student (All admins can edit)
- **FM-02**: Track monthly fee per student (All admins can edit)
- **FM-03**: Mark fees as paid/unpaid
- **FM-04**: Set and track fee due dates (Only Admin)
- **FM-05**: Calculate total fees collected (monthly + admission)
- **FM-06**: Edit fee records (Only Admin)

### 2.6 Dashboard & Reporting
- **DR-01**: Main dashboard showing:
  - Total seats count (current: 160+)
  - Reserved seats count
  - Available seats count
  - Total fees collected (current month)
  - Pending fees amount
  - Active students count
- **DR-03**: Export reports to PDF/Excel/CSV

### 2.7 System Configuration
- **SC-01**: Add more seats (expand beyond initial 160)
- **SC-02**: Configure seat numbering system
- **SC-03**: Set default fee amounts (only admin)
- **SC-04**: Configure payment reminder schedules
- **SC-05**: User management (add/edit users)(Only Admin)

### 2.8 Offline Functionality
- **OF-01**: Full app functionality without internet
- **OF-02**: Data integrity validation

## 3. Non-Functional Requirements

### 3.1 Performance
- **NF-01**: App loading time < 3 seconds
- **NF-02**: Seat status updates in real-time (< 2 seconds)
- **NF-03**: Handle 160+ seats with smooth scrolling
- **NF-04**: Search functionality response < 1 second

### 3.2 Reliability
- **NF-05**: 99.5% uptime for online services
- **NF-06**: Data integrity during sync operations
- **NF-07**: Automatic backup of local data
- **NF-08**: Crash-free experience

### 3.3 Usability
- **NF-09**: Intuitive interface requiring minimal training
- **NF-10**: Consistent design across all screens
- **NF-11**: Clear error messages and guidance
- **NF-12**: Accessibility compliant (WCAG 2.1 AA)

### 3.4 Security
- **NF-13**: Individual secure authentication for each user
- **NF-14**: Data encryption at rest and in transit
- **NF-15**: Audit logs for all critical operations
- **NF-16**: Password policy enforcement
- **NF-17**: Session timeout (15 minutes inactivity)

### 3.5 Scalability
- **NF-18**: Support for unlimited seat expansion
- **NF-19**: Handle up to 10,000 student records
- **NF-20**: Support additional admin users in future

